DOCUMENT();
loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "PGchoicemacros.pl",
  "MathObjects.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl"
);

Context("Numeric");

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$n = random(2,5,1);
$x0 = random(1,3,1);
$k = random(2,3,1);
$x1 = $k*$x0;
$c = random(1,7,1);
$a = $c/($x0**($n-1));

$m1 = $n*$c;
$m2 = $n*$c*($k**($n-1));

Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT

Given a power function of the form \( f(x)=ax^n \), with
\( f'($x0) = $m1 \) and \( f'($x1) = $m2 \), find \( n \) and \( a \).

$BR$BR
\( n = \) \{ ans_rule(25) \} 
$BR$BR
\( a = \) \{ ans_rule(25) \}

END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;

ANS(Compute( $n )->cmp() );
ANS(Compute( $a )->cmp() );

$v1 = $k**($n-1);
$n1 = $n-1;
$ad = "\frac{$c}{" . $x0**($n-1) . "}";

Context()->texStrings;
SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$PAR SOLUTION $PAR

Since \( f(x)=ax^n \), \( f'(x)=anx^{n-1} \).
We know that \( f'($x0)=(an)$x0^{n-1} = $m1 \), and 
\( f'($x1) = (an) $x1^{n-1} = $m2 \).  Therefore,
\[ \frac{f'($x1)}{f'($x0)} = \frac{$m2}{$m1} = $v1. \]
But 
\[ \frac{f'($x1)}{f'($x0)} = \frac{(an)$x1^{n-1}}{(an)$x0^{n-1}} =
   $k^{n-1}, \]
so \( $k^{n-1} = $v1 \), and so \( n = $n \).
$PAR
Substituting \( n=$n \) into the expression for \( f'($x0) \), 
we get \( $n a $x0^{$n1} = $m1 \), so \( a = $ad \).

END_SOLUTION


